metadata.name: Firework #76
metadata.description:
Welcome to "Firework," a generative art piece inspired by the beauty and significance of fireworks.

Fireworks have long been associated with celebrations and special occasions, and they are particularly well-known for their role in ringing in the new year. As we approach New Years 2023, it's a perfect time to reflect on the meaning and significance of fireworks in our culture along with our individual accomplishments made throughout this past year.

In this art piece, I aim to capture the essence of fireworks and their role in our lives. Through the use of vibrant colors, dynamic patterns, and random elements, I hope to create a sense of excitement and wonder that is evocative of the joy and wonder that fireworks bring to our celebrations.

I hope you enjoy "Firework" and that it helps you to appreciate the beauty and significance of this past year along with the coming new year.

metadata.name: Computing memory #104
metadata.description:
This creation takes Penghu, Taiwan, my hometown as the theme, and uses the style of expired films to reconstruct the scene in my memory.
During the creative process, I think about how "mechanism" and "choice" affect the scene in my memory, I also asked myself in the process of creation, did I discover the appearance left in my memory after this work or was it the appearance I hoped to see?

metadata.name: Para Metric #170
metadata.description: This collection of NFTs is based on an elementary mathematical principle; a parametric equation. Despite the simplicity of the principle, the results are simply stunning. All kinds of intricate shapes and patterns are formed by drawing random dots a parametric equation solely based on sines and cosines. Combined with a simple bright shape in the background, the art pieces are created. Every piece is highly unique can with different backgrounds and amount of shapes. I hope you enjoy the pieces!

metadata.name: Mar de lã #191
metadata.description:
"Once upon a time, in a land far, far away, there was a magical kingdom known for its beautiful landscapes and mystical creatures. The kingdom was ruled by a kind and fair queen, who loved nothing more than to spend her days exploring the vast and varied terrain of her realm.

One day, the queen was wandering through a particularly cold and snowy region of the kingdom when she came upon a strange sight. Instead of snow, the ground was covered with soft, fluffy balls of wool, as if the earth itself had been transformed into a giant ball of yarn.

The queen was fascinated by this curious phenomenon, and she decided to follow the trail of wool to see where it led. After walking for some time, she came upon a beautiful lake, the surface of which was frozen solid. But instead of ice, the lake was made entirely of woolen fibers, swirling and twirling in the gentle breeze.

The queen marveled at the sight, and she couldn't help but reach out and touch the soft, velvety surface of the woolen lake. As she did, she felt a warmth and comfort wash over her, as if the wool were alive and pulsing with energy.

Over the years, the queen visited the woolen lake often, always feeling a sense of peace and contentment when she was near it. And as the years went by, the people of the kingdom began to flock to the woolen lake, seeking the same sense of warmth and comfort that the queen had found.

The woolen lake became a beloved and sacred place in the kingdom, and it was known throughout the land as the "mar de lã" - the sea of wool. And so it remained, a magical and mystical place that brought joy and happiness to all who visited."
_AI GPT

metadata.name: Terraced #87
metadata.description:
terraced craters
towering mountains
tranquil colors
dimetric

* this is an animated artwork, the animation loops, its duration depends on the piece, it can be paused by pressing 'p'
* this is a somewhat interactive artwork, click and drag to rotate around/above the object, scroll to zoom in/out
* the current view can be downloaded by pressing 'd'

I began exploring terraced reliefs 3 years ago, starting with lines and cellular noise, and eventually flat colors that turned into subtle gradients.
During that time, the visual concept oscillated between minimalism and busy images. I dropped the cellular noise, replacing it with 2D simplex noise modifying points on the dual grid.
The result is finally something that produces the iterations that keep me happy, something soothing and quiet. Spend some time with it, see how the light changes the landscape.

Best viewed in landscape mode, 3/2 or 16/9.

metadata.name: The Fringe #147
metadata.description:
We are innately aware of our bodies' position through perception of space. If we are visibly surrounded by walls with flooring under, a ceiling above, and a window facing the sky, we know we are inside of an enclosed space, with a view of outside. But how does a room stopped being an enclosed space? Can a space with 3 walls be considered a room? If we are surrounded by walls but our ceiling is gone, then are we inside or outside? This is an exploration on the edges of our ability to perceive space. The fringes that instill some fear in our mind. And that fear is failing to make sense of our position in a space that slowly loses its tangibility.
